file=Brand Studio/lena/marketplace/copywriting/SKILL.md · h=name: copywriting\ntype: marketplace\nstatus: copied verbatim\nsource: https://skillsmp.com/creators/pikakit/agent-skills/agent-skills-copywriting\nsource_repo: https://github.com/pikakit/agent-skills/tree/main/.agent/skills/copywriting\nauthor: pikakit\ncopied_verbatim: true\nfulfills_catalog_entry: copywriting-frameworks (VYON_Skills_Catalog_Full_v2.html, lena/Brand Studio)\nassigned_agent: lena (Brand Studio / Brand Voice)\nportable: true — pure framework content, no company specifics\ndate_added: 2026-07-07 · ym(:yvon-compile metadata (auto-derived from skill content 2026-07-20 — review welcome; body verbatim)=tier: 2\ndescription: "**Required:** None — Copywriting is a knowledge-based skill with no external dependencies."\ntriggers: [copywriting, tired of slow builds?, every second wasted costs $x, introducing [product], our product is great, cut build time by 73% in 48 hours]\n\n<!--\nUnmodified copy of "copywriting" (pikakit/agent-skills), fulfilling the catalog's\ncopywriting-frameworks slot (AIDA, PAS + conversion patterns; this adds BAB/4Ps/4Us/FAB\nand validation rules). Chosen for its deterministic framework-per-content-type selection\nand testable validation rules — the structure layer that pairs with lena's voice layer:\nrun this for STRUCTURE, then voice-guides + humanic-writing for HOW IT SOUNDS.\nNOTES FOR THIS SYSTEM:\n1. Source references its home repo's skills (seo-optimizer, studio, ai-artist) and an\nengineering-spec rules file not copied here — read as pointers, not local skills.\nIn this department: SEO → kai; visual design → atlas/pixel; ad images → pixel.\n2. The OpenTelemetry audit-logging section is the source repo's infrastructure convention —\ntreat as optional; our equivalent is the ordinary output note.\n3. The catalog protocol's "draft 3 variants → hand to nate for test" lives in lena's\nrouting (operational/skill), not inside this verbatim copy: produce variants per\nrequest, and conversion tests route to nate.\n-->\n · c—c:Copywriting — Conversion Formulas=> 6 proven formulas. Benefit-first. Specific claims. One CTA per piece.\n · tb=\| # \| Question            \| Options                           \| · tb=\| --- \| ------------------- \| --------------------------------- \| · tb=\| 1 \| Target Audience?    \| Demographics / Pain points / Role \| · tb=\| 2 \| Core Product Value? \| Primary benefit / USP             \| · tb=\| 3 \| Content Type?       \| Landing / Email / Ad / Headline   \| · tb=\| 4 \| Primary CTA?        \| Buy / Sign Up / Read More         \| · tb=\| 5 \| Brand Tone?         \| Professional / Casual / Urgent    \| · ### Prerequisites=**Required:** None — Copywriting is a knowledge-based skill with no external dependencies.\n\n · tb=\| Content Type               \| Formula  \| Steps                                     \| · tb=\| -------------------------- \| -------- \| ----------------------------------------- \| · tb=\| Landing pages, ads         \| **AIDA** \| Attention → Interest → Desire → Action    \| · tb=\| Email, sales pages         \| **PAS**  \| Problem → Agitate → Solution              \| · tb=\| Testimonials, case studies \| **BAB**  \| Before → After → Bridge                   \| · tb=\| Long-form sales            \| **4Ps**  \| Promise → Picture → Proof → Push          \| · tb=\| Headlines                  \| **4Us**  \| Urgent + Unique + Useful + Ultra-specific \| · tb=\| Product descriptions       \| **FAB**  \| Feature → Advantage → Benefit             \| · ### When to Use=**Selection is deterministic:** same content type = same formula, every time.\n\n · tb=\| Owned by This Skill                \| NOT Owned                              \| · tb=\| ---------------------------------- \| -------------------------------------- \| · tb=\| Formula selection per content type \| SEO keyword research (→ seo-optimizer) \| · tb=\| Headline validation (4Us)          \| Visual design (→ studio)               \| · tb=\| Copy validation (5 rules)          \| A/B test infrastructure                \| · tb=\| Anti-pattern detection             \| Image generation for ads (→ ai-artist) \| · ### System Boundaries=**Pure decision skill:** Produces formula frameworks and validation. Zero side effects.\n\n · tb=\| Step          \| Purpose         \| Guidance                           \| · tb=\| ------------- \| --------------- \| ---------------------------------- \| · tb=\| **A**ttention \| Grab interest   \| Bold headline with specific number \| · tb=\| **I**nterest  \| Build curiosity \| Key benefit statement              \| · tb=\| **D**esire    \| Create want     \| Social proof, testimonials         \| · tb=\| **A**ction    \| Drive CTA       \| Single, clear next step            \| · tb=\| Step         \| Purpose        \| Guidance                       \| · tb=\| ------------ \| -------------- \| ------------------------------ \| · tb=\| **P**roblem  \| Name the pain  \| "Tired of slow builds?"        \| · tb=\| **A**gitate  \| Intensify pain \| "Every second wasted costs $X" \| · tb=\| **S**olution \| Present fix    \| "Introducing [Product]"        \| · tb=\| Step       \| Purpose                        \| · tb=\| ---------- \| ------------------------------ \| · tb=\| **B**efore \| Current painful state          \| · tb=\| **A**fter  \| Desired outcome with specifics \| · tb=\| **B**ridge \| Your solution connects them    \| · tb=\| Step          \| Focus                 \| · tb=\| ------------- \| --------------------- \| · tb=\| **F**eature   \| What it is            \| · tb=\| **A**dvantage \| Why it matters        \| · tb=\| **B**enefit   \| How it helps the user \| · tb=\| Dimension          \| Question            \| Pass/Fail \| · tb=\| ------------------ \| ------------------- \| --------- \| · tb=\| **U**rgent         \| Why act now?        \| Binary    \| · tb=\| **U**nique         \| What's different?   \| Binary    \| · tb=\| **U**seful         \| What's the benefit? \| Binary    \| · tb=\| **U**ltra-specific \| What exactly?       \| Binary    \| · ### Headline Validation (4Us)=```\n❌ "Our Product is Great"           → 0/4 Us\n✅ "Cut Build Time by 73% in 48 Hours" → 4/4 Us\n```\n\n · tb=\| # \| Rule            \| Check                                       \| · tb=\| --- \| --------------- \| ------------------------------------------- \| · tb=\| 1 \| Benefit-first   \| Benefits precede features                   \| · tb=\| 2 \| Single CTA      \| One call-to-action per piece                \| · tb=\| 3 \| Specific claims \| Numbers, percentages, or concrete outcomes  \| · tb=\| 4 \| No jargon       \| Conversational tone over corporate language \| · tb=\| 5 \| Read-aloud test \| No awkward phrasing when spoken             \| · tb=\| Code                       \| Recoverable \| Trigger                            \| · tb=\| -------------------------- \| ----------- \| ---------------------------------- \| · tb=\| `ERR_INVALID_REQUEST_TYPE` \| No          \| Request type not supported         \| · tb=\| `ERR_MISSING_CONTENT_TYPE` \| Yes         \| Content type not provided          \| · tb=\| `ERR_UNKNOWN_CONTENT_TYPE` \| No          \| Content type not in supported list \| · tb=\| `ERR_MISSING_DRAFT`        \| Yes         \| Draft required for validation      \| · tb=\| `ERR_EMPTY_DRAFT`          \| Yes         \| Draft is empty                     \| · ### Error Taxonomy=**Zero internal retries.** Deterministic; same inputs = same output.\n\n · tb=\| ❌ Don't                 \| ✅ Do                            \| · tb=\| ----------------------- \| ------------------------------- \| · tb=\| Features first          \| Benefits first                  \| · tb=\| Multiple CTAs           \| One clear action                \| · tb=\| Vague claims ("faster") \| Specific numbers ("73% faster") \| · tb=\| Corporate jargon        \| Conversational tone             \| · tb=\| Event               \| Metadata Payload                                 \| Severity \| · tb=\| ------------------- \| ------------------------------------------------ \| -------- \| · tb=\| `formula_selected`  \| `{"formula": "PAS", "content_type": "email"}`    \| `INFO`   \| · tb=\| `validation_passed` \| `{"content_type": "headline", "score": "4/4"}`   \| `INFO`   \| · tb=\| `violations_found`  \| `{"rule": "benefit-first", "severity": "error"}` \| `WARN`   \| · ### Audit Logging (OpenTelemetry)=All copywriting outputs MUST emit `formula_selected`, `validation_passed`, or `violations_found` events when applicable.\n\n · tb=\| File                                             \| Description                                             \| When to Read        \| · tb=\| ------------------------------------------------ \| ------------------------------------------------------- \| ------------------- \| · tb=\| engineering-spec.md (source repo `rules/`)        \| Full engineering spec: contracts, security, scalability \| Architecture review \| · tb=\| Item            \| Type  \| Purpose                     \| · tb=\| --------------- \| ----- \| --------------------------- \| · tb=\| `seo-optimizer` \| Skill \| SEO-friendly copy structure \| · tb=\| `studio`        \| Skill \| Design + copy integration   \| · tb=\| `ai-artist`     \| Skill \| Image generation for ads    \| · ### 🔗 Related=⚡ PikaKit v3.9.206\n